DESCRIPTION
workflow.Default(), etude init docs, and golden tests still describe/scaffold the older six-stage test-plan/test workflow using dev-coder and dev-test-writer, while the checked-in .etude/workflow.yaml and current dogfood loop use plan -> implement -> verify -> docs -> review with dev-executor and dev-qa. Align the canonical generated default with the actual Etude-native loop so downstream consumers, including the Xenota dev projection, can treat Etude workflow config as the authority without xrs/repertoire assumptions. Scope: update workflow.Default() to emit plan/implement/verify/docs/review; use roles plan/diff/verify/docs-diff/review; use dev-executor for implement and dev-qa for verify; replace test-plan-rubric scaffolding with verify-rubric; update golden workflow tests and implemented init docs; reconcile product/dogfood planning references that still present test-plan/test as the default or explicitly mark them historical/planned if not current.

DESIGN
Goal: Align workflow.Default() (what `etude init` scaffolds) with the shipped Etude-native loop in .etude/workflow.yaml — plan/implement/verify/docs/review — replacing the stale 6-stage test-plan/test default that used dev-coder/dev-test-writer.

Approach (stage shape only; NOT gate blocks):
New Default() emits 5 stages, matching the stage shape of .etude/workflow.yaml:
  1. plan     produces plan      inputs [task]            skill dev-planner    eval rubric evals/plan-rubric.md
  2. implement produces diff     inputs [plan,repo-state] skill dev-executor
  3. verify   produces verify    inputs [plan,diff]       skill dev-qa         eval rubric evals/verify-rubric.md
  4. docs     produces docs-diff inputs [diff]            skill dev-docs-writer optional true
  5. review   produces review    inputs [diff,plan,verify] skill dev-pr-reviewer eval pairwise
Stage order matches .etude/workflow.yaml (docs before review). review now consumes verify (a valid earlier-produced role).

Rationale for NOT emitting gate blocks: the bead scope lists stage/skill/role/eval changes only. .etude/workflow.yaml's gate tiers + abstraction prose are this repo's dogfood-specific customization layered on top of the scaffold; baking etude's tiers into every scaffolded project is out of scope. Default() stays gate-free as today; "same five-stage shape" = same stage sequence/skills/produces/evals.

